Loops and iteration#
- Indefinite loop: (while, break, continue) statement / boolean
- Definite loop: (for, in) statement
- Counting in a loop
- Finding the average in a loop
- Filtering in a loop
- None type : to be used on boolean and Note type
-Iteration variables
-Loop idioms

Updating variables
# This is an infinite loop
n = 10
while True:
    print(n, end=' ')
    n = n - 1
print('Done!')

### Debugging
We don't want to do that line by line. We can can by bisection instead.
